HEADWORD: Cicatrix
<hw>Ci*ca"trix</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Cicatrices</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The pellicle which forms over a wound or breach
of continuity and completes the process of healing in the latter, and
which subsequently contracts and becomes white, forming the
scar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cicatrizant</ent>⟦br⟧
